<p>Investors don’t need a paternalistic SEC protecting them from more information, only blatantly false information. The marketplace of ideas works better than ever, certainly better than a 1930s-erected regulatory structure.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://memesteading.com">Gordon Mohr</a>
